  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">WASH Services for South Sudanese Refugees in Al Nimir, East Darfur</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">In response to the recent influx of South Sudanese refugees into East Darfur, Sudan, CIS plans to address the life-saving WASH needs based on the inter-agency assessment conducted in July 2016 and subsequent monitoring and verification of the population and needs as they have moved from their original place of arrival in Abu Sinaidira to El Ferdous town and Old Raja camp in Khor Omer. CIS will work as part of a consortium led by UNHCR to support initial site development and critical life-saving assistance for 10,000 refugees (6more than 8,000 currently verified existing caseload plus and 4,000 anticipated new arrivals) in Al Nimir. The proposed project has identified 15,500 beneficiaries to benefit from the project activities in Al Nimir area-Maali administrative unit, Asalaya locality in East Darfur State including Al Nimir camp and the surrounding catchment area of Al Nimir. The target group will be served in Al Nimir camp (13 Km South of Eldein town) through number of WASH activities related to water supply and community level sanitation shall benefit all the community members in the catchment area. CIS will work with national partner Al Swaid Al-Khadra Organization (AAO) to increase access to safe water supply promote improved hygiene practices and improve sanitation conditions by constructing latrines and managing cleaning campaigns.</narrative>
  </description>
